-- Stenson Wins Golf’s Tour Championship, $10 Million Playoff Bonus
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-09-22T21:51:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-22/stenson-wins-golf-s-tour-championship-10-million-playoff-bonus.html
Henrik Stenson won golf’s season-ending Tour Championship, earning the Swede a $10 million bonus
for topping the FedEx Cup standings after the U.S. PGA Tour’s
four playoff events.  Stenson finished the tournament at East Lake Golf Club in
Atlanta with a four-round total of 13-under-par 267 for a three-shot win over Jordan Spieth and  Steve Stricker .  In addition to the bonus, Stenson collected $1.44 million
for his third title on the PGA Tour. Stenson, 37, also won the
second playoff event, the Deutsche Bank Championship, his first
win on the tour since 2009.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  